snippet.textDisplay:
Dalgona is basically pressed melted sugar. the coffee gets its name because the color of the coffee is similar to the dalgona itself,,, so just in case you want to make dalgona:
__________________
HOW TO MAKE DALGONA:


materials:
- sugar
- basking soda
- a stove
- a ladle or a very small frying pan
- something to press the dalgona (i use this aluminum steel looking lid from my rice bowl)
- a chopstick or something to stir
- non-stick pan (i use a plate but the pros use those oven pans
- optional: cookie cutters of choice
__________________
instructions:
1. grab a ladle or a small frying pan (very small frying pan) and put a spoonful of sugar (it does not matter how much, it depends on the size you want to make the final product)
2. Melt the sugar and make sure to stir
3. once completely melted, add a small amount of baking soda and stir fast (the color will change to a lighter brown. also, be quick because it will solidify if youre too slow)
4. pour the mixture on to the baking/oven pan and very quickly press your lid type thing to make it flat (be sure to take it off instantly or else it will solidify on the lid)
5. snippet.textOriginal:
Dalgona is basically pressed melted sugar. the coffee gets its name because the color of the coffee is similar to the dalgona itself,,, so just in case you want to make dalgona: 
____________________
HOW TO MAKE DALGONA:


materials:
- sugar
- basking soda
- a stove
- a ladle or a very small frying pan
- something to press the dalgona (i use this aluminum steel looking lid from my rice bowl)
- a chopstick or something to stir
- non-stick pan (i use a plate but the pros use those oven pans
- optional: cookie cutters of choice
____________________
instructions: 
1. grab a ladle or a small frying pan (very small frying pan) and put a spoonful of sugar (it does not matter how much, it depends on the size you want to make the final product)
2. Melt the sugar and make sure to stir
3. once completely melted, add a small amount of baking soda and stir fast (the color will change to a lighter brown. also, be quick because it will solidify if youre too slow)
4. pour the mixture on to the baking/oven pan and very quickly press your lid type thing to make it flat (be sure to take it off instantly or else it will solidify on the lid)
5. (optional) use a cookie cutter to gently press on a shape (do not press all the way through, but enough to make an imprint,,, you dont have to do this step but when they sell it here, they have these imprints and if you can chip the dalgona into the shape that is imprinted, you get another dalgona)
